consorts: {{hlist|[[Radha]]|[[Rukmini]]|[[Satyabhama]]|[[Kalindi]]|[[Jambavati]]|[[Nagnajiti]]|[[Mitravinda]]|[[Bhadra (Krishna's wife)|Bhadra]]|[[Lakshmana (Krishna's wife)|Lakshmana]] and [[Junior wives of Krishna|16,000 – 16,100 Junior queens]]|ref| name=hawley12|{{cite book |title=The Divine Consort: Rādhā and the Goddesses of India|author=John Stratton Hawley, Donna Marie Wulff |publisher=Motilal Banarsidass Publisher |date=1982 |isbn=978-0-89581-102-8 |page=12}}|</ref>}} {{refn|group|=|note|Radha is seen as Krishna's lover-consort.
